			<p class="card-text"> <br> Roulette is a very simple game, and really is a game of pure luck. In this game, you take your betting ammout, and place it on either a colour, high/low, row, section or single number, and the dealer will spin the roulette wheel and drop a stainless steel ball into it, waiting until the spin has completed and the ball has landed on a number. 
			
			<br> <br> The house will pay out based on the % chance behind your bet, for example, if you bet on a single number, the house will pay out 35:1, wheras if you bet on a colour or high/low, the house will pay out 1:1 and return to you double your initial bet.

			<br> <br> Some casinos use roulette tables with double zeros, also known as American roulette, this improves the house edge* and means that you have less chance of winning, due to there being two rouge numbers instead of just the one green zero.
			
			<br> <br> *house edge - This is the Casinos chance of beating you, the house edge will always be better than the players, if not they would not be able to operate. 
			
